{
  "stem": "10478.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I still remember that he bought a second-hand steam train, train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he played with that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he let  us play with it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we usually we were-- we looked at it, how he did it-- does that himself.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We watched him, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was scared with the steam that came out, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he enjoyed it, yeah, yeah, yeah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my family was religious from upbringing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My, my, my parents, we all were members of the Reformed Church, a small church in Maastricht.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They practiced their religion by going twice to church on Sunday and by-- at home, you know, educating us, us in the Bible, Old and New Testament, and reading the Bible, and praying on the table, yeah.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we, we read quite a bit out of the Old and New Testament, yes--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--on the-- on the table, when we have our sitting together.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most, most, most was read by  my parents, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the moral lesson we got from the readings, and also from the teaching of our parents, was to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] look after the poor, look after the people who are homeless, and so on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were an example to that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we, we followed that  later on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That started very early in  my life, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not before the war because there was practically no racism.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, we didn't knew-- didn't even know who was a Jew or not.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after the-- 1932, when we had an influx of Jewish immigrants from Germany, then we became aware at what racism was and what hate was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the only data we, we got was to listen to radio  and the papers what happens in Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was an eye-opener for us, what racism really was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The persecution of the Jews, the way that they had to flee-- leave the country, and came to, to Holland and other countries, maybe.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and there was quite an influx, yeah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not at all.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we-- our city hall set up a committee when I was 19 years of age to look after those people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they asked me if-- our church asked me to be a representative there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that committee  had regular meetings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we discussed what-- how to handle the influx and what to do with those people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was upsetting, of course.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the real death came after Hitler came into Holland, yeah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "19 years.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was one, one of the members of that committee to look after the people who came from Germany and who were-- looked-- who were looking for places to, to stay, and whatever, yeah.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was formed with the city of [NON-ENGLISH]-- the city of Maastricht.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not that I'm aware of, no.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had-- we hadn't ever had a problem, no.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The only way I [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] know about it is, of course, that people always talk about-- that's, that's a Jew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I found that-- I found that quite disturbing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, if, if, if, if, for example, somebody bought an-- a, a shirt in a store, if it was done in the store   of Mrs.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Johnson, they said, I went-- he, he, he, he-- they treated me not well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But if it was a Jew, they said, the Jew got me again, selling me a bad shirt.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that is, in my eyes, is a form of racism.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the press, you know, in, in the press and by radio, in-- well, when I was 13, 14 years old.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we, we heard his yelling on the radio all the time, you know, if, if he was [INAUDIBLE] speaking engagement somewhere.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we heard about his stand on, on Jews and other minority groups in, in our papers and also in our radio broadcast.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was very anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- as a matter of fact, you know, and it was all known in Holland that he was planning to kill the Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We, we only became aware of that when they occupied Holland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they make propaganda with showing the, the, the movie and things like that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had big billboards with all kinds of slogans against the Jews, Nazi [INAUDIBLE] mind, yeah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah, of course.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were concerned about happened to the Jews and also what's going to happen to all of us, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we have-- we all had fears that he would enter Holland, you know, and occupy Holland, and that he would do the same thing in Holland as that he did  in Germany.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were-- had not close connections with our neighbors, really.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
